  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reduced Vulnerability by Introducing Viable Economies (REVIVE) Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community-wide, Internally Displaced Persons, Women, Populations Affected by Conflict/Crisis/War, Indigenous People, Children/Youth, Populations Affected by Natural/Environmental Disaster, Other Marginalized Groups</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective #1: To rehabilitate riverbanks, water tributaries and gullies along Silway&#x2010;Klinan River System in 13 barangays by establishing gabions and planting of fruit trees and bamboos.

Objective #2:  To provide alternative livelihood opportunities to 390 of families through cash crop production assistance.

Objective #3: To capacitate farmer leaders and local officials in 13 barangays to advocate for local government&#x2019;s action in enhancing barangay disaster risk reduction programs and enforcement of environmental policies and ordinance.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to address and limit the impacts of flooding along the Silway-Klinan River System. The project supports the planting and maintenance of bamboo, forest and fruit tree seedlings while also providing training in proper waste management procedures for businesses and households.</narrative>
  </description>
